  "text": ". The validated scoring system of the questionnaire was used to stratify patients into either \"low-risk\" or \"high-risk\" for having OSA. [CITATION_1] Subjects who scored positive in two or more categories were considered as \"high-risk\" for OAS, otherwise they were considered \"lowrisk\". The findings of the CATH were reported by the interventional cardiologist, and CAD was defined as having at least one coronary vessel with >50% intraluminal stenosis.",
